        {
            "id": "0aa1abbb4dde457ecdc5f5618aa2140855434fba",
            "author": {
                "_account_id": 6159,
                "name": "Flavio Percoco",
                "display_name": "flaper87",
                "email": "fpercoco@redhat.com",
                "username": "flaper87"
            },
            "real_author": {
                "_account_id": 6159,
                "name": "Flavio Percoco",
                "display_name": "flaper87",
                "email": "fpercoco@redhat.com",
                "username": "flaper87"
            },
            "date": "2016-05-16 19:43:59.000000000",
            "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\n(2 comments)\n\n-1 mostly on the github link and the proposal below.\n\nHere's a counter proposal. Based on the facts that we have the following things already:\n\n* Reno\n* Tags in commit messages\n* Dashboard (or at least a way to group/filter reviews on gerrit)\n\nHow would folks feel about not requiring any lite-spec to be written except for the patch itself?\n\nThe content that will go into the lite-spec might as well go in the patch's commit message. We can tag the review as \"lite-spec\" and we can use (and we should) reno to write all the impacts the change has.\n\nAs far as listing the changes go, we can easily generate indexes from the merged changes by either filtering on the commit message tag, the reno file, etc.\n\nI just feel that duplicating reviews for small changes is a waste of reviewer's time, at least right now. We made this mistake in Mitaka and we made it even harder. Not having to review 2 patches for a single change would be neat.\n\nThoughts?",
            "accounts_in_message": [],
            "_revision_number": 1
        },
        {
            "id": "79f2a2440006ad9c0954e9a79d507adc488c5550",
            "author": {
                "_account_id": 8158,
                "name": "Hemanth Makkapati",
                "email": "makstacker+osgerrit@gmail.com",
                "username": "hemanth.makkapati"
            },
            "real_author": {
                "_account_id": 8158,
                "name": "Hemanth Makkapati",
                "email": "makstacker+osgerrit@gmail.com",
                "username": "hemanth.makkapati"
            },
            "date": "2016-05-17 16:59:30.000000000",
            "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(5 comments)\n\nI like what Flavio is suggesting although I'm not too familiar with how the generation bit works. +2 to the idea of contributors and reviewers not having to deal with two patches for a small change.\n\nSo, Flavio let me know if my understanding of what you propose is correct:\n* Fill out the lite-spec template as a part of the commit message\n* Tag the commit with something that identifies it as a lite-spec\n* Include reno notes as part of the commit for release notes describing the change\n* Once the change is merged, generate a lite-spec artifact for publishing.",
            "accounts_in_message": [],
            "_revision_number": 1
        },
        {
            "id": "d99ab523b059e843771749c3a1f8848f0dcf2270",
            "author": {
                "_account_id": 8122,
